🧩 Bit 1: SAP Security Fundamentals
🔹 What to learn:
SAP security = Protecting SAP systems, data, and users
Key components:
Authentication (Who are you?)
Authorization (What can you access?)
Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability (CIA triad)
🔹 Important SAP Concepts:
User Types: Dialog, System, Communication, Service
Roles & Profiles (PFCG)
Authorization Objects
🔹 Key Transactions:
SU01 → User management
PFCG → Role management
SU53 → Authorization check
